latestIgtvVideos.title: Sharing our piece of heart ❣️
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Marriage is the most important day for most of the people , so it should always reflect your belief system. Today as we celebrate 6 months of our wedding I would like to share the things we did . They might sound unconventional to many but they truly reflect our beliefs.

1. I lived together with my now husband before marriage for years ( on and off ) to know him better.

2. We didn't opt for ' Kundali Match ' .

3. We didn't distribute wedding cards made up of paper and instead sent digital invitation. 

4. I didn't wear red and wore blue simple  saree for my wedding. I also wore pastel green Lehenga ( not expensive at all )  for the dinner party. I wanted to wear my mom's wedding lehenga but it was not in a wearable condition so I wore her wedding dupatta. 

5. I didn't buy any extra saree or suit because according to me it means blocking money . I literally bought only 1 saree, 2 lehengas and 1 suit in total.

6. I kept the makeup minimal for the day function. It was like ' lagaya hai but nahi bhi lagaya ' 😁. 

7. I didn't buy any expensive jewelry and bought something very economical( 5k) from chandni chowk market of Delhi. If we talk about gold jewellery then I bought only a gold chain mangalsutra .

8. I didn't go for elaborate mehendi on hands. I chose such a little design for my feet that my mom had to intervene 😂. There was no one in mehedi ceremony except me and my family.

9. There was no haldi rasam.

10. For the engagement ceremony we went out for dinner and exchanged rings in the front of 8-10 people.

11. There was no exchange of money or gifts at all .

12. There were only 35-40 people present at our wedding .

13. There was no touching of feet from my side but didn't force my husband to ' not touch' as it was his choice. 

14. The wedding was in an Arya Samaj Mandir .

15. The decoration was only marigold flowers on one of the walls for the pictures.

16. There was no serious environment and everyone made jokes and was in a happy mood.

17. My parents did my kanyadan because I was in no mood for argument or discussion with the pandit but I don't believe in it. 

(CONTINUED IN THE COMMENTS )
